question.value:
The primary outcome is the COS score (out of 29) for each journal. The secondary outcomes are: 
1. journals requirements for disclosing conflicts of interest (score out of 4 from the ICMJE);
2. difference in COS and ICMJE scores obtained in February 2020 and June 2020
3. difference in COS and ICMJE scores obtained in February 2020 and June 2020 depending on whether a journal received LTE-1 or LTE-2
4. the acceptance rate of the 20 LTEs describing the COS score in comparison to other medical and health science journals; 
5. differences in the acceptance rate of LTEs based on whether the journal received LTE-1 or LTE-2.

